Serialized Form

  • Package frame

    • Class frame.GameFrame extends javax.swing.JFrame implements Serializable

    • Class frame.GamePanel extends javax.swing.JPanel implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • MAX_HELP_SCREENS

          int MAX_HELP_SCREENS
          Amount of help screens there are.

        • gameState

          int gameState
          Which screen the game is currently in.

          The screens are:

          0 - Main Menu

          1 - Adventure Game

          2 - Help

          3 - High Scores

          4 - Exit Screen

          5 - Removed

          6 - Regular Battle

          7 - Boss Battle

          8 - Game Over

          9 - Regular Message Screen

          10 - End Game Message Screen

          11 - Won Game

          12 - Exit

        • screenState

          int screenState
          Required to track position on help screens.

        • backgrounds

          java.awt.Image[] backgrounds
          All the backgrounds used throughout the game.

        • menuButton

          java.awt.Image[] menuButton
          The images for the two states of the menu buttons, clicked and unclicked.

        • arrowButton

          java.awt.Image[][] arrowButton
          The images for the two states of the four arrow buttons in the game screen.

        • battleButton

          java.awt.Image[] battleButton
          The images for the two states of the buttons available in combat.

        • help

          java.awt.Image[] help
          The images for the help screens.

        • muteButton

          java.awt.Image[] muteButton
          The images for the two states of the mute button.

        • backButton

          java.awt.Image[] backButton
          The images for the two states of the buttons for exiting the game to main menu.

        • mouse

          GameMouse mouse
          Provides interaction between the panel and the mouse.

        • gameTimer

          javax.swing.Timer gameTimer
          Allows the screen to be refreshed every set amount of time.

        • battleTimer

          javax.swing.Timer battleTimer
          Restricts the length of the battle.

        • buttons

          GamePanel.Button[][] buttons
          A 2D array of all the buttons. The first dimension is the screen as specified by gameState, the second is the button number.

        • highScores

          int[] highScores
          All the high scores at the start of the program.

        • game

          GameGraphics game
          Does processing of everything related to interaction between the character and map.

        • message

          java.lang.String message
          The message to be displayed by the message screen.

        • messageCharacter

          int messageCharacter
          The character saying the message.

        • characters

          java.awt.Image[] characters
          The characters for saying messages.

        • mute

          GamePanel.MuteButton mute
          The mute button for the game
